{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"896d0f12-96e2-42a4-8fdf-b1fab5546f55","agentId":"a2cceb1c12f4a6bcd","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Do focused WEB research (WebSearch + WebFetch; cite URLs). Do not answer from memory alone. Context: a local self-improving agent (\"Yogi\") on a 16 GB MacBook (one model at a time: qwen3:8b ~5-6 GB, nomic-embed-text ~0.3 GB). Token-space compounding (memory + verifier-fed skills + a Think/NoThink navigator) is already certified end-to-end. I must choose and scope the NEXT compounding layer. Compare two candidates and recommend which to build next:\n\n(i) **Per-domain weight distillation within 16 GB.** Is it feasible to distill/fine-tune a small per-domain student (e.g. a 0.5B–3B model, or a LoRA adapter on qwen3:8b) ON-DEVICE on a 16 GB Apple-silicon Mac, given the one-model-at-a-time constraint? Cover: LoRA/QLoRA memory math for these sizes; Apple-silicon training paths (MLX-LM LoRA, llama.cpp finetune, unsloth/mac); realistic time/quality; whether inference of a distilled student + adapter fits alongside nomic; the failure modes (catastrophic forgetting, tiny-data overfit). When is distillation worth it vs token-space memory/skills?\n\n(ii) **Outcome-learned routing.** Route Think/NoThink (and which skill to load) by recorded past pass/fail per task-class rather than a heuristic. Cover: contextual-bandit / LinUCB / Thompson routing for LLM inference-mode selection; cost-aware routing (accuracy vs latency/tokens); how much it helps vs a good heuristic; cold-start; any 2024-2026 work on learned reasoning-effort routing for reasoning models.\n\nEND WITH a concrete recommendation: which to build next for Yogi on 16 GB, why, and a minimal first implementation sketch. Cite URLs throughout. Return findings only; do not edit files."},"uuid":"bad255d5-dcfa-4828-9406-d63629bba8a2","timestamp":"2026-06-21T06:42:55.347Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b71